<body>
    <div class="container">
        <%- include('../partials/header') %> 

        <div class="wraper">
            <!-- What's PID -->
            <fieldset>
                <legend>What's Perid</legend>
                <p>
                    Perid is the Personal Id that contains some basic information about you. <br>
                    You can share it with people to get in touch with you.
                </p>
            </fieldset>
            <div class="spacer"></div>
            <!-- API Documention -->
            <fieldset>
                <legend>API Documention</legend>
                <p>
                    Perid also provides an API that you can use in your app to find a user registered is our databases. <br>
                    The usage of it is fairly simple;
                    <h5>> Get user by Id</h5>
                    Getting a user by Id requires a GET request to <code>https://perid.tk/api/[pid]</code></p>
                    <p>
                        The API returns a json object that contains: <br>
                        An <code>error</code> boolean, if true there was an error if not request operated successfully. <br>
                        If there was an error the api returns a <code>message</code> string that contains a message explaining the error. <br>
                        If there was no error the api returns a boolean <code>foundId</code> that specifies if the given id is registered to a user. <br>
                        If a user is found then the api returns an object <code>Id</code> that contains the found user.
                    </p>
                    The json object that the API returns looks like this: <br>
                    <div class="code-container" style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <code>
                            {<br>
                                &emsp;"error": false,<br>
                                &emsp;"foundId": true,<br>
                                &emsp;"Id": {<br>
                                &emsp;&emsp;"firstName": "John",<br>
                                &emsp;&emsp;"middleName": "",<br>
                                &emsp;&emsp;"lastName": "Smith",<br>
                                &emsp;&emsp;"birthdate": "2001-05-28T00:00:00.000+00:00",<br>
                                &emsp;&emsp;"phone": "202-555-0104",<br>
                                &emsp;&emsp;"email": "jhon.smith@outlook.com",<br>
                                &emsp;&emsp;"avatarImageBase64": "data:image/jpeg;charset=utf-8;base64,[avatar-base64-encoded]"<br>
                                &emsp;&emsp;"qrImageBase64": "data:image/png;charset=utf-8;base64,[qr-base64-encoded]"<br>
                                &emsp;}<br>
                            }
                        </code>
                    </div>
                    <br>
                    <p>
                        To display user's avatar (or user's qr code) with html img tag just but the <code>avatarImageBase64 (or qrImageBase64)</code> value in src attribute. <br>
                        If the found user doesn't have an avatar, <code>avatarImageBase64</code> will be null.  If user's qr code fail to generate it will be null as well.
                    </p>
                </p>
            </fieldset>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
